      "sha": "ed4a90a4d34b2acb943ba1a7e974294f5fb0390c",
      "message": "Install udev rule as part of Debian pkg install (#28)\n\nInstead of requiring the user of the package to run a script, have\r\nthe udev rule installed as part of the package.\r\n\r\nThe udev will be installed as\r\n    /lib/udev/rules.d/60-ros-<rosdistro>-kobuki-ftdi.rules\r\nIf more than one ROS distribution is installed on the same system,\r\nthe older distribution udev rules file will be used as the :=\r\noperator is used.\r\nSee: https://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/utils/kernel/hotplug/udev/udev.html\r\n\r\nAdditional References:\r\n    http://www.reactivated.net/writing_udev_rules.html\r\n    http://manpages.ubuntu.com/manpages/xenial/man1/dh_installudev.1.html",
      "files_changed": 2,
